# Architecture

The project has two main components that communicate over a network:

## Feed Program

- Runs on a lightweight edge device (e.g. Raspberry Pi 5) with an attached camera
- Captures a live video feed and streams it to the processing server
- Receives back processed video and audio output from the server
- Drives local audio playback and video projection based on the server's response

## Processing Server

- Receives the video stream from the feed program
- Runs detection/analysis models on the incoming frames (facial recognition, gesture detection, motion tracking, etc.)
- Maps detection results into appropriate video and audio output
- Streams the generated output back to the feed program

## Data Flow

```
Feed Program                   Processing Server
┌──────────┐   video stream    ┌──────────────┐
│ camera   │ ───────────────▶  │ detection    │
│          │                   │ models       │
│ speakers │ ◀───────────────  │ (face,       │
│ projector│   audio + video   │  gesture,    │
└──────────┘   output          │  motion)     │
                               └──────────────┘
```

## Guidelines

- Keep feed-program code lightweight — heavy computation belongs on the server
- Detection models and mapping logic live exclusively in the processing server
- The feed program should be resilient to temporary network interruptions
- Use clear interface boundaries between the two components (e.g. shared protocol definitions)
